    <!-- Hero Section -->
    <section class="hero" id="about">
        <div class="hero-content">
            <h2>Senior Program Manager | AI-Enabled Delivery</h2>
            <p>I'm Arachelvi (Chelvi), a Senior Program Manager with 11 years orchestrating global enterprise programs that shouldn't have been possible. 800-location rollouts, critical infrastructure built in two weeks, 98% on-time delivery.<br><br>I'm now diving into AI-enabled program management — exploring how intelligent automation and Gen AI can transform how we plan, execute, and scale programs. Recently completed my Master's in Health Informatics with a focus on Gen AI.<br><br>Ready to lead the next generation of smarter, faster program execution.</p>
            <div class="hero-buttons">
                <button class="btn btn-primary">Download Resume</button>
                <button class="btn">View Work</button>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Main Content -->
    <div class="container">
        <!-- About Me Section -->
        <section class="section">
            <h3>From Dentist to AI-Enabled Program Leader</h3>
            <p>I didn't start out in tech. I'm a Doctor of Dental Surgery from India, and my journey into program management wasn't planned — it was a pivot driven by curiosity and a love for building scalable systems.</p>
            <p>Over the past 11 years, I've led enterprise-scale technology programs across healthcare, retail, telecom, and cloud infrastructure. My dental background gave me something unexpected: deep listening skills, empathy for diverse stakeholders, and the ability to work under pressure while maintaining precision. I gained regulatory discipline (HIPAA compliance), attention to detail in complex environments, and the patience to explain technical concepts to non-technical audiences. These human-centered skills became a real competitive advantage.</p>
            <p>Now I'm merging everything — my healthcare knowledge, 11 years of execution excellence, listening and empathy skills, and a newfound passion for AI and intelligent automation. I'm fascinated by how Gen AI can make program delivery more predictable, more efficient, and less about firefighting.</p>
            <p>This portfolio shows how I'm evolving — taking what I've learned building impossible programs with people at the center, and exploring what's next with AI.</p>
        </section>

        <!-- Key Highlights Section -->
        <section class="section">
            <h3>Key Highlights</h3>
            <div class="highlights">
                <div class="highlight-card">
                    <i class="ti ti-target"></i>
                    <h4>Strategic Planning</h4>
                    <p>I develop enterprise roadmaps that align technical initiatives with business goals. At NTT Data, I designed phased strategies for 800+ location SD-WAN rollouts and 105+ hospital healthcare programs. I translate complexity into executive dashboards, govern multi-million dollar budgets, and manage dependencies across vendors and timelines.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="highlight-card">
                    <i class="ti ti-users"></i>
                    <h4>Stakeholder Management</h4>
                    <p>I lead cross-functional coordination across matrixed environments with competing priorities. Embedded at Google's REWs, I partnered directly with executives to optimize workspace strategies while managing field teams and vendors. I orchestrated 800+ carrier locations and 620+ retail stores by building trust through clear communication and consistent delivery.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="highlight-card">
                    <i class="ti ti-chart-line"></i>
                    <h4>Data-Driven Decisions</h4>
                    <p>I use metrics and dashboards to inform strategy and prioritization. At Google, I built real-time program dashboards tracking deployment status, risks, and milestones for executives. I leverage Tableau, Power BI, and advanced Excel to visualize program health, identify bottlenecks, and forecast outcomes. My data discipline ensures decisions are evidence-informed.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="highlight-card">
                    <i class="ti ti-rocket"></i>
                    <h4>Agile Delivery</h4>
                    <p>I manage complex launches and critical initiatives under extreme pressure. I led emergency network infrastructure for COVID-19 hospitals in partnership with US Army Corps of Engineers — standing up 10 locations in under two weeks. Delivered 100+ AV deployments across Google offices with zero disruption. Expert in Scrum, Lean, and PMBOK frameworks.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Featured Projects Section -->
        <section class="section" id="projects">
            <h3>Featured Projects</h3>
            <div class="projects">
                <div class="project-card">
                    <h4>Emergency Hospital Network Infrastructure Deployment</h4>
                    <p class="date">2020 — 2 weeks</p>
                    <p>Partnered with US Army Corps of Engineers to deploy critical network infrastructure across 10 COVID-19 field hospital locations under impossible timelines. Coordinated vendors, managed supply chain logistics, and maintained 24/7 execution momentum. 10 hospitals operational in 2 weeks | 100% on-time delivery under crisis conditions | Mentored 4 coordinators who advanced to PM roles.</p>
                    <div class="tags">
                        <span class="tag">Crisis Management</span>
                        <span class="tag">Vendor Coordination</span>
                        <span class="tag">Mentoring</span>
                    </div>
                    <a href="project1-covid-hospital.html" class="project-link">View Project Details →</a>
                </div>
                <div class="project-card">
                    <h4>Global SD-WAN Implementation</h4>
                    <p class="date">2019-2022 — Sr. Project Manager</p>
                    <p>Led vendor management, program oversight, and coordinator training for multi-year SD-WAN rollout across Americas, Europe, Asia, and Australia. Built self-sustaining Microsoft Teams scheduling tool enabling 20+ engineers across USA and APAC zones to sign up for sites by timezone. Tool required only monitoring. Accelerated execution speed | Generated real-time dashboards for invoicing | Reduced scheduling overhead by 80%.</p>
                    <div class="tags">
                        <span class="tag">Global Rollout</span>
                        <span class="tag">Tool Development</span>
                        <span class="tag">Vendor Management</span>
                    </div>
                    <a href="project2-sdwan-global.html" class="project-link">View Project Details →</a>
                </div>
                <div class="project-card">
                    <h4>Cisco to Juniper Migration — Nordstrom Retail Network</h4>
                    <p class="date">2019-2021 — Sr. Project Coordinator</p>
                    <p>Managed 620+ store network migration across all US Nordstrom locations. Intervened in critical vendor-engineering conflict that nearly halted the project using mediation and stakeholder alignment. Successfully restarted project execution and rebuilt trust. Project resumed successfully | Customer expanded scope | Received company award for conflict resolution | Zero major retail disruptions.</p>
                    <div class="tags">
                        <span class="tag">Conflict Resolution</span>
                        <span class="tag">Stakeholder Management</span>
                        <span class="tag">Award Winner</span>
                    </div>
                    <a href="project3-nordstrom-migration.html" class="project-link">View Project Details →</a>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Skills Section -->
        <section class="section" id="skills">
            <h3>Skills & Expertise</h3>
            <div class="skills-grid">
                <div class="skill-group">
                    <h4>Program Management</h4>
                    <ul class="skill-list">
                        <li>Roadmap Planning & Governance</li>
